ght-hard and\nintermediate states. Their hosts show ongoing star formation in the central\nkiloparsecs. We discuss the above scenario, its potential links with the galaxy\nevolution picture and the possible presence of accretion state transitions in\nAGN, as suggested by the growing population of changing-look quasars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Apr 2021 18:00:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-28"}
